Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @panko breadcrumbs{25%g}, @water{2%tbsp} and @salt{1/4%tsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British beef mince{240%g}. Season with @ground black pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person. Set aside.
> The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

In another bowl, mix the @bulgogi sauce{100%g} with the @olive oil{2%tbsp}, then add the @British chicken thighs{2}. Mix well to coat, then cover and set aside.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging.

== Sesame Wedges ==

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over half the @roasted white sesame seeds{14%g}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.
> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Chicken ==

Lay the chicken thighs flat onto another baking tray and drizzle over any remaining marinade from the bowl.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until browned and cooked through, ~{16-18%minutes}.
> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Alternatively, cook them on the BBQ if you'd prefer.

== Slaw ==

Meanwhile, trim and peel the @carrot{1}(trimmed and peeled). Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Thinly slice the @radishes{100%g}. Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1} and reserve 1 leaf per person, then thinly slice the rest.

Pop all your salad veg into #large serving bowl{} and set aside until serving.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

== Burgers ==

Once hot, add the burgers and fry until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-14%minutes} in total. Carefully turn them every ~{3-4%minutes} and lower the heat if needed.
> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, lower the heat and add three quarters of the @bulgogi sauce{64%g}. Turn to glaze the burgers in the sauce.

Alternatively, cook them on the BBQ if you'd prefer.

When almost ready, halve the @burger buns{2}. Pop into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Bulgogi Mayo ==

In a small bowl, mix the remaining bulgogi with half the @mayonnaise{64%g} and the @water{1%tbsp} for the mayo. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then drizzle over the salad. Sprinkle over the remaining sesame seeds and toss to coat.

== Assembly ==

Spread the remaining mayo over the cut sides of your buns, then top each base with a reserved lettuce leaf, bulgogi burger and bun lid.

Serve with the teriyaki chicken, salad and wedges.

Enjoy!

== Teriyaki Chicken ==

Serve the @teriyaki sauce{75%g}.